  "function_path": "compiler/rustc_borrowck/src/region_infer/mod.rs",
  "function_name": "check_type_tests",
  "justification": "This function validates whether type-outlives relationship tests generated during type checking are satisfied by inferred region values. It takes an immutable reference to the region inference context (&self), an inference context (&InferCtxt), an optional mutable vector for propagating outlives requirements to closures, and a mutable buffer for collecting error reports. It maintains a deduplication set of (erased generic kind, lower bound region, span) triples to avoid duplicate error reports. For each registered type test, it: (1) converts the generic kind to a concrete type, (2) evaluates its verify bound against the inferred lower-bound region, (3) if satisfied, skips the test, (4) if not satisfied but in a closure, attempts to promote the type test into a closure outlives requirement, (5) if promotion succeeds, skips the test, (6) otherwise, erases and anonymizes the generic kind's regions, checks the deduplication set, and if the error is novel, pushes a failure entry into the errors buffer."
}

